    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s03.2.12" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Manifold Air Temperature (MAT) Sensor</title>
        <figure id="f3450003015" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ09/J09016.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>MAT sensor</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>The MAT sensor is a thermistor sensor. The ECM monitors the MAT signal to control injector timing and fuel
            rate during cold starts. The ECM also uses the MAT signal to control Exhaust Gas Recirculating (EGR) valve
            position and intake throttle control. The MAT sensor is mounted in the top left side of the intake manifold.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
